hybridized language that relies on the listener's ability to speak both languages. a bilingual speaker in delhi, might for example, say "mera fever bahut bad hai" (my fever is very bad) which mixes english with hindi 50-50 in spite of the fact that perfectly good words exist for both 'fever' and 'bad' in hindi. this hybrid is sometimes referred to as 'hinglish.'it seems that english and hindi are indeed converging among the bilingual sections of society. while english, as a distinct language, is here to stay for now, it appears that it will eventually over hundreds of years be absorbed 